A Soweto mother who was arrested for selling atchar without a permit has vented her anger against the police. Courtesy #DStv403 SOWETO - A Soweto mother who was arrested for selling atchar without a permit, has vented her anger against the police. Footage of 53-year-old Thandi Thabede’s arrest nearly two weeks ago, caused outrage online. Many South Africans came to her aid with donations and she was later released on a warning. READ: Criminals ask for alcohol first during hotel robbery For Thabede, the arrest conjured up feelings of the past. When Thabede arrived at court the next day, a lawyer told her to go home, and wait for a call if needed. She’s thanked social media campaigner, Tumi Sole, and numerous South Africans who've made, several food and cash donations.